# Kubernetes_Vertical_Pod_Autoscaling_Using_RL
Installing kubectl using curl
This set of instructions will guide you on how to install kubectl on a 
Linux machine using curl.

Prerequisites
A Linux machine with root access.
curl and sudo packages installed.
Step 1: Download kubectl
Run the following command to download the latest stable version of 
kubectl:

bash
Copy code
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s 
https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
Step 2: Install kubectl
Run the following command to install kubectl:

bash
Copy code
sudo install -o root -g root -m 0755 kubectl /usr/local/bin/kubectl
This will install kubectl to /usr/local/bin/kubectl and set the necessary 
permissions.

Verify kubectl installation
To verify that kubectl is installed and working properly, run the 
following command:

css
Copy code
kubectl version --client
This should display the client version of kubectl you just installed.

Congratulations! You have successfully installed kubectl on your Linux 
machine.





